column2: AT DEEPEST AREA WITH VAN DORN- NEAR BOTTOM
GILAS LAKE AT DEEPEST AREA WITH INTEGRATED SAMPLER
Sunny morning- light breeze with no boat traffic. Saw a bald eagle and loons
Somewhat overcast- slight chop- one other boat on the lake. Saw two loons.
overcast- breezy and cool- I saw a loon
overcast- with scattered showers- light wind from northwest- I saw 1 loon. Surface temp was 74 degrees
Beautiful day- sunny- light wind- I saw one osprey.
Somewhat overcast today with light wind- about 4 or 5 people fishing.
It was overcast and cool today. I saw ducks and a bald eagle It was overcast and cool today. I saw ducks and a bald eagle. There are floating bunches of grassy weeds.
Clear sky- slight breeze- one other boat on lake. I saw one loon and a osprey.
Weather was windy and overcast (from NW 15 mph). Water seems to be more brown than usual. I saw two loons and a osprey.
Sunny with 15mph wind from southeast. I saw loons an eagle- osprey and lots of muskrats.
Beautiful day partly cloudy with a steady breeze from the southeast. I saw loons- an eagle and a large pine snake. water temp was 79 degrees.

Overcast and cool- saw loons- water level is extremely high this spring. Water color seems to be more yellow- brown (tannic) than usual. Overcast and cool today- saw 2 loons. Water seems to be more yellow- brown (tannic) than usual. Water level is the highest that I have seen since I bought this place in 1983. Surface water Temp. 60.9 degrees.
75 degrees- partly cloudy- 10-15 mph breeze from the west. I saw one loon 75 degrees- partly cloudy- 10-15 mph breeze from west. Water temp was 72 degrees. I saw one loon.

Partly cloudy- brisk wind from west and about 71 deg. I saw a bald eagle and a loon. Water temp. was 74 deg. Partly cloudy- brisk wind from the west- Temp. was 72 deg. I saw a bald eagle and a loon. Lots of weeds floating around
